# PR Descriptions

When writing a pull request description (draft or final), always output it as **markdown inside a fenced code block** so it can be copied and pasted directly into GitHub.

## Format

- Wrap the full description in a ` ```markdown ` code fence
- Use GitHub-flavored markdown: `##` headings, bullet lists, checkboxes
- Include at least **Summary** and **Test plan** sections
- Prefer concise bullets over long prose

## Example shape

````markdown
```markdown
## Summary
- What changed and why

## Test plan
- [ ] How to verify
```
````

## Do not

- Render the description as normal chat markdown only (harder to copy cleanly)
- Add surrounding commentary inside the code fence—keep the fence contents PR-ready
